snippet.textDisplay: Hans Raj is a very talented punjabi singer- I dont know what all these other singers who are not punjabi have to come in and desecrate such great work.  Hans Raj on his own here would be a much better quality song than bringing this substandard bollywood noises in. The reason pakistani coke studio is superior is because they are true the punjabi culture and dont mix it with bollywood type songs. I have no issue with bollywood songs- but they should remain in there own category. What sounds good to rest of india does not necessarily sound good to a punjabi! Punjabi culture is so strong in arts and music that any punjabi you mix with rest of india it sounds good to rest of india. But it actually brings the punjabi song quality a step down. If you want to bring good quality music like in pakistan coke music then leave punjabi singers to sing there own true to the punjabi culture unadultered by bollywood. Punjabi music rules pakistan and india-- do not bring other elements unless you can match the standard and quality of punajbi singers otherwise not only do you a diservice to punjabis but also to rest of india--. Leave pure milk to itself-- no need to add water and get a substandard product-- even though it is still too rich a concentration for an ant.
